  <p>If your preferred resources are not available via a framework or if you&rsquo;re looking to purchase a small or urgent order of books, you may want to compare third party suppliers or wholesalers. You can research these online or find an educational trade supplier recommended by the <a href="https://www.besa.org.uk/">British Educational Suppliers Association</a>.</p>

  <p>Before you use this route, make sure you&rsquo;ve got at least 3 quotes from a range of suppliers and evaluated their offers against price and quality to get the best value for money. Do not be afraid to negotiate lower prices or enhanced support from suppliers.</p>


  <h3>Buy direct from publishers</h3>

  {{ govukWarningText({
    html: 'Selecting this route means you&rsquo;ll need to lead your own procurement. You can find step-by-step guidance to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/buying-for-schools">support you through the procurement process</a>.',
