  <p>If you need help selecting the right resource for your school, you can invite publishers to give advice on which products would suit your specifications.</p>

  <p>To get the most out of your funds, sales leads can offer a range of services to support you when choosing and embedding the resource in your school. You can contact sales leads via each publisher&rsquo;s website or <a href="https://publishers.org.uk/about-us/members-and-affiliates/">The Publishers Association</a>.</p>

  <p>Many publishers can help aggregate funds with other schools and academies to save you money. Even if it&rsquo;s a single purchase, it&rsquo;s worth negotiating discounts and comparing quotes and support services between publishers to get the best value for money. </p>

  <p>For example, if you&rsquo;re investing in an ongoing contract, consider securing an agreed discount for top-ups in the future.</p>



  <h2 id="choose">Choosing the right supplier</h2>

  <p>Once you&rsquo;ve found the right way to buy, use a <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/school-procurement-bid-evaluation-scoring-summary">supplier scorecard</a> to compare suppliers' bids during a procurement process.</p>

  <p>You should consider if suppliers:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>offer the level of curriculum coverage and support you need</li>
    <li>match the needs of your school and students</li>
    <li>offer the same cost compared to similar products</li>
    <li>offer an after-sales service and the cost involved</li>
  </ul>



